<h4>Renjie Chang, M.D., M.S., Founder & President</h4>
<p>
    Dr. Chang started the company in 1999, determined to apply the knowledge and skills she had learned
    from a long career in the field of Obstetrics and Gynecology and in the pharmaceutical industry. In
    the past three decades, she worked as an OB-GYN in the Peking Union Hospital in China, a faculty member
    of OB-GYN at University of Oklahoma Health Sciences Center, and a drug developer at the Abbot Laboratories
    in Chicago. She established Lavax, Inc. to develop an innovative vaginal microbicide for preventing HIV
    with grants from NIH and Gates Foundation. While developing the antiviral drug, she invented the all
    natural Nu-Eve suppository as a spin-off. Because this product is a personal health care product, not a
    drug, it can be marketed to benefit consumers much sooner.

